a. Monitor System Resources

df: Shows disk space usage of file systems.
Example: df -h

du: Displays disk usage of files and directories.
Example: du -sh folder/

free: Shows memory (RAM) usage.
Example: free -h

uptime: Displays how long the system has been running and load average.

vmstat: Reports memory, CPU, and process statistics.

b. Archiving and Compression

tar: Archives multiple files/directories into one file (can also compress).
Example: tar -czvf backup.tar.gz folder/

zip: Compresses files into a .zip archive.
Example: zip -r files.zip folder/

unzip: Extracts .zip archives.
Example: unzip files.zip

c. Usage, Options, and Sample Outputs

Use -h for human-readable output.

Use -r for recursive operations on directories.

Sample outputs show size, usage percentage, and resource status, helping with system health monitoring.
